 (Thailand)|PPTV]]\n|-\n|[[Turkey]]\n|[[beIN SPORTS]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[United States|US]]\n|[[ESPN]]\n|-\n|[[ESPN+]]\n|-\n|Latin America\n|[[ESPN Latin America|ESPN]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Worldwide (selected countries only)\n|[[Rai Italia]]\n|-\n|Serie A Pass\n|}\n\nIn the 1990s, Serie A was at its most popular in the United Kingdom when it was shown on ''[[Football Italia]]'' on [[Channel 4]], although it has actually appeared on more UK channels than any other league, rarely staying in one place for long since 2002. Serie A has appeared in the UK on [[British Satellite Broadcasting|BSB]]'s The Sports Channel (1990\u201391), [[Sky Sports]] (1991\u201392), Channel 4 (1992\u20132002), [[Eurosport]] (2002\u201304), [[Setanta Sports]] and [[Bravo (British TV channel)|Bravo]] (2004\u201307), [[Channel 5 (UK)|Channel 5]] (2007\u201308), [[BT Sport ESPN|ESPN]] (2009\u201313), [[BT Sport]] (2013\u20132018), [[Eleven Sports Network]] (2018), [[Premier Sports|Premier]] and [[FreeSports]] (2019\u2013present).<ref name=\"UK rights\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44818136|title=Serie A: Eleven Sports gain TV rights from BT in three-year deal|date=13 July 2018|work=BBC Sport|accessdate=13 July 2018|publisher=British Broadcasting Corporation}}</ref>\n\n==Champions==\n:{{main|List of Italian football champions}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:12%;\"| Club\n! Winners\n! Runners-up\n! Championship seasons\n|-\n| '''[[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]]'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 35\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 21\n| [[1905 Prima Categoria|1905]], [[1925\u201326 Prima Divisione|1925\u201326]], [[1930\u201331 Serie A|1930\u201331]], [[1931\u201332 Serie A|1931\u201332]], [[1932\u201333 Serie A|1932\u201333]], [[1933\u201334 Serie A|1933\u201334]], [[1934\u201335 Serie A|1934\u201335]], [[1949\u201350 Serie A|1949\u201350]], [[1951\u201352 Serie A|1951\u201352]], [[1957\u201358 Serie A|1957\u201358]], [[1959\u201360 Serie A|1959